													<p style="margin-bottom:1em;margin-top:0em;"><img src="evernotecid://2469044D-762E-4C34-AD45-671C16ABF2D0/ENResource/p1167" style="border: 0px none; max-width: 100%; height: auto;" x-evernote-mime="image/png" width="660" height="56" class="en-media" /></p>

													<p style="margin-bottom:1em;margin-top:0em;"><span style="float:right;margin:0px 0px 8px 10px;"><a shape="rect" href="#" style="text-decoration:none;color:rgb(237, 70, 36);"><img src="evernotecid://2469044D-762E-4C34-AD45-671C16ABF2D0/ENResource/p1158" style="border: 0px none; text-decoration: none; max-width: 100%; height: auto;" x-evernote-mime="image/jpeg" width="120" height="120" class="en-media" /></a></span>The <a style="background-image:url(http://www.savagehomeautomation.com/universal/images/core-resources/icons/blk_ko_18/open-off-site.png);background-color:transparent;padding-right:13px;margin-right:1px;background-position:100% 50%;background-repeat:no-repeat no-repeat;text-decoration:none;color:rgb(237, 70, 36);" shape="rect" href="http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/B005CLMJLU/savagehomeaut-20" target="_blank">Edimax EW-7811Un 150 Mbps Wireless 802.11bgn USB Adapter</a> is a popular choice for use with the Raspberry Pi.  Here is what this little adapter has going for it:  </p>

													<ul style="list-style-type:square;margin:1em 0px;padding:0px 0px 0px 2em;">

														<li>It is on the <a style="background-image:url(http://www.savagehomeautomation.com/universal/images/core-resources/icons/blk_ko_18/open-off-site.png);background-color:transparent;padding-right:13px;margin-right:1px;background-position:100% 50%;background-repeat:no-repeat no-repeat;text-decoration:none;color:rgb(237, 70, 36);" shape="rect" href="http://elinux.org/RPi_VerifiedPeripherals#Working_USB_Wifi_Adapters" target="_blank">approved list</a> of known working peripherals. <span style="display:inline;"><img src="evernotecid://2469044D-762E-4C34-AD45-671C16ABF2D0/ENResource/p1065" style="border: 0px none; max-width: 100%; height: auto;" x-evernote-mime="image/png" width="12" height="14" class="en-media" /><img src="evernotecid://2469044D-762E-4C34-AD45-671C16ABF2D0/ENResource/p1065" style="border: 0px none; max-width: 100%; height: auto;" x-evernote-mime="image/png" width="12" height="14" class="en-media" /><img src="evernotecid://2469044D-762E-4C34-AD45-671C16ABF2D0/ENResource/p1065" style="border: 0px none; max-width: 100%; height: auto;" x-evernote-mime="image/png" width="12" height="14" class="en-media" /></span></li>

														<li>Works directly attached to the Raspberry Pi USB port. <span style="display:inline;"><img src="evernotecid://2469044D-762E-4C34-AD45-671C16ABF2D0/ENResource/p1065" style="border: 0px none; max-width: 100%; height: auto;" x-evernote-mime="image/png" width="12" height="14" class="en-media" /><img src="evernotecid://2469044D-762E-4C34-AD45-671C16ABF2D0/ENResource/p1065" style="border: 0px none; max-width: 100%; height: auto;" x-evernote-mime="image/png" width="12" height="14" class="en-media" /><img src="evernotecid://2469044D-762E-4C34-AD45-671C16ABF2D0/ENResource/p1065" style="border: 0px none; max-width: 100%; height: auto;" x-evernote-mime="image/png" width="12" height="14" class="en-media" /><br clear="none" /></span><em>(Some network adapters used with the Pi require an external USB powered hub)</em> </li>

														<li>The latest Raspbian distributions come with the driver for this adapter pre-installed.  <span style="display:inline;"><img src="evernotecid://2469044D-762E-4C34-AD45-671C16ABF2D0/ENResource/p1065" style="border: 0px none; max-width: 100%; height: auto;" x-evernote-mime="image/png" width="12" height="14" class="en-media" /><img src="evernotecid://2469044D-762E-4C34-AD45-671C16ABF2D0/ENResource/p1065" style="border: 0px none; max-width: 100%; height: auto;" x-evernote-mime="image/png" width="12" height="14" class="en-media" /><img src="evernotecid://2469044D-762E-4C34-AD45-671C16ABF2D0/ENResource/p1065" style="border: 0px none; max-width: 100%; height: auto;" x-evernote-mime="image/png" width="12" height="14" class="en-media" /></span></li>

														<li>It's tiny!  It does not block access to the second USB port on the Raspberry Pi (<em>Model B</em>).  <span style="display:inline;"><img src="evernotecid://2469044D-762E-4C34-AD45-671C16ABF2D0/ENResource/p1065" style="border: 0px none; max-width: 100%; height: auto;" x-evernote-mime="image/png" width="12" height="14" class="en-media" /><img src="evernotecid://2469044D-762E-4C34-AD45-671C16ABF2D0/ENResource/p1065" style="border: 0px none; max-width: 100%; height: auto;" x-evernote-mime="image/png" width="12" height="14" class="en-media" /></span></li>

														<li>Supports 150 Mbps 802.11n  <span style="display:inline;"><img src="evernotecid://2469044D-762E-4C34-AD45-671C16ABF2D0/ENResource/p1065" style="border: 0px none; max-width: 100%; height: auto;" x-evernote-mime="image/png" width="12" height="14" class="en-media" /></span></li>

														<li>Backward compatible with 802.11b/g  <span style="display:inline;"><img src="evernotecid://2469044D-762E-4C34-AD45-671C16ABF2D0/ENResource/p1065" style="border: 0px none; max-width: 100%; height: auto;" x-evernote-mime="image/png" width="12" height="14" class="en-media" /></span></li>

														<li>Internal chip antenna  <span style="display:inline;"><img src="evernotecid://2469044D-762E-4C34-AD45-671C16ABF2D0/ENResource/p1065" style="border: 0px none; max-width: 100%; height: auto;" x-evernote-mime="image/png" width="12" height="14" class="en-media" /></span></li>

														<li>Affordable / Reasonably priced at $8.79 USD (<a style="background-image:url(http://www.savagehomeautomation.com/universal/images/core-resources/icons/blk_ko_18/open-off-site.png);background-color:transparent;padding-right:13px;margin-right:1px;background-position:100% 50%;background-repeat:no-repeat no-repeat;text-decoration:none;color:rgb(237, 70, 36);" shape="rect" href="http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/B005CLMJLU/savagehomeaut-20" target="_blank">Buy it here</a>) <span style="display:inline;"><img src="evernotecid://2469044D-762E-4C34-AD45-671C16ABF2D0/ENResource/p1065" style="border: 0px none; max-width: 100%; height: auto;" x-evernote-mime="image/png" width="12" height="14" class="en-media" /><img src="evernotecid://2469044D-762E-4C34-AD45-671C16ABF2D0/ENResource/p1065" style="border: 0px none; max-width: 100%; height: auto;" x-evernote-mime="image/png" width="12" height="14" class="en-media" /><img src="evernotecid://2469044D-762E-4C34-AD45-671C16ABF2D0/ENResource/p1065" style="border: 0px none; max-width: 100%; height: auto;" x-evernote-mime="image/png" width="12" height="14" class="en-media" /></span></li>

													</ul>

